                <note rend="inline" type="source">551.5F1/175: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-07T13:00:00+00:00"
                            >October 7, 1931—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 7—11:49 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>404. The British Government has postponed further consideration of the silver
                    conference to a date after the election on October 27. Subsequently, the
                    Secretary of State for the Dominions intends to discuss with me the possibility
                    of a conference under Canadian auspices.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
